### Bonus Q2 — Rank All The Things

Same table but with a ranking column — NULL for non-members, ranked for members only.

```sql
WITH full_table AS ( ... ),
membership_table AS (
    SELECT customer_id, order_date, product_name, price,
        CASE
            WHEN order_date >= join_date THEN 'Y'
            ELSE 'N'
        END AS membership_status
    FROM full_table
)
SELECT *,
    CASE
        WHEN membership_status = 'N' THEN NULL
        ELSE DENSE_RANK() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id, membership_status
            ORDER BY order_date
        )
    END AS ranking
FROM membership_table;
```

**Approach:**
- Built on top of Bonus Q1 using a second CTE
- `CASE WHEN membership_status = 'N' THEN NULL` assigns NULL to all non-member rows
- `PARTITION BY customer_id, membership_status` resets ranking per customer AND per membership status — this ensures Y rows always start from rank 1

**Result:**
| customer_id | order_date | product_name | price | membership_status | ranking |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| A | 2021-01-01 | sushi | 10 | N | null |
| A | 2021-01-01 | curry | 15 | N | null |
| A | 2021-01-07 | curry | 15 | Y | 1 |
| A | 2021-01-10 | ramen | 12 | Y | 2 |
| A | 2021-01-11 | ramen | 12 | Y | 3 |
| A | 2021-01-11 | ramen | 12 | Y | 3 |
